kubectl apply -f liveness.yaml
kubectl get pod liveness-probe-demo -w
After 30s the file is deleted → liveness fails → pod restarts. Watch it with kubectl get pod liveness-probe-demo -w

kubectl apply -f readiness.yaml
kubectl get pod readiness-probe-demo -w
Pod won't receive traffic for first 20s. Watch with kubectl get pod readiness-probe-demo -w — you'll see 0/1 Running then flip to 1/1

kubectl apply -f startup.yaml
kubectl get pod startup-probe-demo -w
Startup probe allows up to 60s for the app to start. Only after startup succeeds does liveness take over.
